The paper deals with a problem of Private Information Retrieval (PIR) with Private Coded Side Information (PCSI) in a multi-server setting. PIR is a well-studied problem in information theory and cryptography, and cs.IT (Information Theory) is a natural fit for this paper. PCSI is a relatively new concept that has gained attention in recent years, and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another relevant category. The problem involves a database and servers, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could also be a relevant category. The paper also proposes new achievability schemes and proof techniques, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
